# prettyping

> a wrapper around the system's "ping" tool.
> It will substitute each ping response line by a colored character, giving a very compact overview of the ping responses.

`prettyping --[no]color`

- Enable/disable color output. (default: enabled)


`prettyping --[no]unicode`

- Enable/disable unicode characters. (default: enabled)

`prettyping --[no]legend`

- Enable/disable the latency legend. (default: enabled)

`prettyping --[no]terminal`

- Force the output designed to a terminal. (default: auto)

`prettyping --last <n>`

- Use the last "n" pings at the statistics line. (default: 60)

Other Parameters passed directly to ping.
